 make sure that people are posting in the right forum.<br>
At the same time we need fewer over lapping forums.<br>
<br>
Contradictorily, I would like to see an &quot;Apprentices Hall&quot; for the misc. &quot;How does this spell work? What does this thing do? Where should I hunt at level xx&quot; as well as a forum for end-game players.  Neither would be passworded, but the end-game players' section should try to keep &quot;lowbie&quot; questions to the other forum.<br>
<br>
Basically the breakdown would be: <br>
------------------ EQ Forums ------------------<br>
General Discussion -- all misc. EQ chat<br>
Apprentices Hall -- don't want to call it newbie because people won't go there for fear of the negative connotation.<br>
Tower of the Arcane -- End Game discussion<br>
Spells &amp; AA -- self explanatory<br>
PvP Discussion and Tactics -- self explanatory<br>
Class Balancing -- self explanatory<br>
Equipment Advice  -- Area to ask about gear questions<br>
Quest and Guide help -- For any questions related to a guide, or a quest.<br>
------------------ OT Forums ------------------<br>
Off Topic Forum -- self explanatory<br>
Polls Forum -- self explanatory<br>
Rant Forum -- self explanatory <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=8991"><br>
